news.title: Meghalaya CM awards land patta to over 100 tribal households in Reserve Gittim
news.para: The CEM is all set to award more than 100 land Pattas to tribal beneficiaries who are the rightful owners in recognition of their long-standing demand for rights over the land.

news.title: Keystone Realtors raises over Rs 190 crore from anchor investors ahead of IPO
news.para: Abu Dhabi Investment Authority, Morgan Stanley and Saint Capital accounted for nearly 35 per cent of the anchor investor portion.

news.title: Seven unsafe buildings in Chandrapur razed, eight others given final notices
news.para: CMC officials said they identified 15 such buildings and served notices to the occupants to vacate them. These included six buildings in Zone-I, eight in Zone-II and a solitary building in Zone-III.

news.title: Telangana: Granite businessmen cry foul over ED raids, say it's 'terrorising'
news.para: Reacting strongly to the searches, the Telangana Granite Industry Owners' Association said the Centre was terrorising the ailing granite industry.

news.title: Granite is new marble of Rajasthan
news.para: Industry estimates that about 4000-5000 new granite units have come up in the state in the past 5-6 years and the production of the dimension stone has also increased from 25 lakh tonnes in 2015-16 to 56 lakh tonnes in 2019-20.

news.title: IIA-Navi Mumbai points out flaws in civic body's draft development plan
news.para: ​NMMC has received a large number of subjections and objections to its DP. The civic body’s 20-year (2018-2038) draft DP has received 15,261 suggestions and objections.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso residents demand tower D be razed and rebuild
news.para: They have instead demanded that the tower should be rebuilt and their apartments restored to them. The 18-storey Tower D, which was evacuated after the February incident, will be demolished.

news.title: Land allotment for poor only after gazette notification: Andhra Pradesh government
news.para: Continuing arguments on behalf of the state government and the CRDA, additional advocate general P Sudhakar Reddy and Kasa Jagan Mohan Reddy argued that the state government is empowered to allot five per cent of land in the capital region for affordable housing.

news.title: Stamp duty collection affected in Gujarat
news.para: ​​Revenue officials of Ahmedabad have put up notices at the offices of two stamp duty (assessment) deputy collectors within the polytechnic campus in Ambawadi.

news.title: Mumbai: Stop-work notice to Bhendi Bazaar redevelopment project revoked
news.para: The Rs 4,000-crore project was brought to a standstill when the BMC followed up on deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis ordering an inquiry into complaints that the Saifee Burhani Upliftment Trust, which is executing the project, had changed the original plans.

news.title: Dubious funds from Chinese entities sent to Telangana-based granite entities: ED
news.para: ED launched the searches at the offices and residential premises of Swetha Granites, Swetha Agencies, Sri Venkateshwara Granites, PSR Granites, Arvind Granites, Giriraj Shipping Agencies & their related entities in Karimnagar & Hyderabad.

news.title: Bank of Baroda lowers home loan rates by 25 basis points to 8.25%
news.para: ​At 8.25 per cent, BoB's rate is lower than that of the segmental leaders SBI and HDFC, whose new pricing is at 8.40 per cent, announced before Diwali and lasting end-December.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires two land parcels in Noida for Rs 377 crore
news.para: Godrej Properties will develop residential group housing on the land parcels located in Sector 146, Noida. Spread over 12.4 acres, the two adjacent land parcels will offer approximately 3.2 million sq ft of development potential.

news.title: Gurugram: 40 building sites flout GRAP rules, penalised Rs 20 lakh
news.para: ​A fine of Rs 50,000 has been imposed on each developer and if they fail to deposit, the same will be recovered during the grant of occupation certificate.

news.title: GNIDA asks Jaiprakash Associates to remove helipad at Jaypee Greens
news.para: The residents’ association of Jaypee Greens had moved the Allahabad high court earlier this year against the helipad operating within a residential colony of both villas and highrises.
